# Backend Data Retention

- Follow `docs/architecture/data-retention.md` as the source of truth for deletion behavior.
- `draft` game deletion is the only allowed hard-delete exception (`DELETE /api/game/setup`).
- Draft setup media deletion (`DELETE /api/game/setup/cells/{cellId}/media`) may hard-delete the storage object plus unlink it from draft state.
- Non-draft games must use soft-delete (`games.IsDeleted`, `games.DeletedAtUtc`) rather than physical deletion.
- Question catalog deletion must be soft-delete (`question_definitions.IsDeleted`, `question_definitions.DeletedAtUtc`), not physical deletion.
- Question enable/disable endpoints are state toggles, not delete semantics.
- Modifier catalog uses archive-ready semantics (`modifier_definitions.IsArchived`); avoid physical delete flows for global modifier definitions.
- Global catalog and identity data (`users`, `question_definitions`, `modifier_definitions`) must not be cascade-deleted by game flows.
- Keep FK delete behavior history-safe: prefer `Restrict`/archive/deactivate for references used by historical records.
- Runtime read paths that drive active behavior must consistently filter soft-deleted rows.
- When delete policy changes, update OpenAPI, generated frontend contracts, tests, and docs in the same task.
